1. WAF vs. RASP
​A WAF (Firewall) can be bypassed by complex payloads. We need a defense that understands the app's internal logic.
​
Protecting the perimeter vs. protecting the heart.
​
WAF filters external traffic; RASP (Runtime Self-Protection) sits inside the app and blocks attacks by watching actual code execution.

2. Secrets Management
​Hardcoding API keys or DB passwords in code leads to catastrophic leaks if the repo is compromised.
​
Centralized, encrypted "vaults" for sensitive credentials.
​
Using tools like HashiCorp Vault or AWS Secrets Manager to inject credentials at runtime.
